Sampling method: Euler A, (found the best results with Eular A, 2nd best DMP++ SDE Karras)

Resolution: if you want to generate girls consistently do portrait 768 which is 624x936 you can mess around with the ratios, landscapes make sure not to go above 1200 res on either height or width and you're all good

Try use "text, signature, watermark, username, artist name, trademark," for negative prompts to not get the signature thing.

items.name: Mekia Cox
items.description:
A commission of @Zorglub.

Mekia Cox is an American actress and dancer, known for her roles in series such as 90210 or The Rookie.

This is a 500-step TI trained on a dataset of 18 images with my usual settings.

For some reason, it seems like reducing the token count to 2 is making my TIs train faster now... I'm not sure, it might be just a lucky streak, but both this TI and Sara Underwood's looked almost ready from a very early stage in their respective trainings. I'll keep testing with this setting.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (m3kiac0x-500:0.99), a woman, RAW, close portrait photo, long brown coat, long haircut, pale skin, slim body, (high detailed skin:1.2), 8k uhd, dslr, soft lighting, high quality, film grain, Fujifilm XT3 sharp focus, f 5.6"

I am from robot workshop and this lora model to create some fake PS1 games, It doesn't look great as pixel art does, but it's very fun to use it.

If you want more realistic results(meaning more like the original games but with lower quality) use also this other pixel art model I made https://civitai.com/models/53252/rwpixelart .

I recomend using Higher quality models like the ChilloutMix https://civitai.com/models/6424?modelVersionId=11745 or Lyriel https://civitai.com/models/22922/lyriel, to have more precision, but any model should work fine with it.

Idea

The idea behind this embedding was to somehow train the negative prompt as an embedding, thus unifying the basis of the negative prompt into one word or embedding.

Usage

To use this embedding you have to download the file aswell as drop it into the "\stable-diffusion-webui\embeddings" folder.

To activate the embedding, you will have to write the name of the file in the negative prompt!

Please put the embedding in the negative prompt to get the right results!

For special negative tags such as "malformed sword", you still need to add them yourself. The negative embedding is trained on a basic skeleton for the negative prompt, which should provide a high-resolution image as a result.

With this version I tried to reduce the amount of vectors used, aswell as the issue with the changing artstyle. The newer version is still a work in progress, but its already way better than the first version. Its in files section!

items.name: Crystal-Clear-Photorealistic
items.description:
Visit Civitai-Crystal team on discord! -news, updates, development, beta testing

Join RunDiffusion on discord! - Auto1111 and InvokeAI in the cloud.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
In the attempt to break the barrier between what's digital and what's real, one model rose to the challenge:


Crystal-Clear-Photorealistic

Now you can generate images as realistic in appearance as your prompt allows it.
This model was not developed for something specific so feel free to try out different things.
From regular portraits to sci-fi aliens in the 5th dimension. It should be able to generate a full body view of things at 704x1088(raw) without any mutations or duplicates.
You can go far, with your creations, by having a good prompt that has a good negative to it as well.

This model is the accumulated result of intense testing, training, feedback and minute detail improvements, upon the Crystal framework, done by an entire team of people over a 3 week period.

__________________________________________________________________________________________________

If your computer is not strong enough, a solution to your problem is RunDiffusion where you can generate your favorite CIVITAI models or you can train new models/LORAs or embeddings.

The model is based on the Crystal-Framework which was created to produce clean, noiseless and unrivaled image quality, while adjusting the colors and sharpness of the image. Although, CC-Photorealistic cannot compete with Crystal-Clear when it comes to producing proper content at very high resolutions, it is unrivaled in the realism domain. Be it food, houses, interiors, animals, nature, photography the choice is yours.
Future versions of this model will tackle the resolution issue !

Note: To produce high realism images, it is advise to use a low CFG ( between 4 and 7).

The model was not tested for mature content or how well it produces it !
Feel free to post your images and feedback, also, don't forget to join the Discord (extra goodies and models available):
Visit Civitai Crystal-Clear on Discord!

If you do plan to include this model in your creations, please show us what you have accomplished! We will also help promote your model if you give us the deserved credit.

items.name: Mirrored Aviator Sunglasses
items.description:
Mirrored Aviator Sunglasses

WHAT?!? The Instagram model porn star guy made a STYLE LoRA?

Indeed I did. I made this for a friend of mine who wanted realistic mirrored sunglasses for their artwork. I had no idea where to start so I went to the Discord and got some great advice, and voila! Mirrored shades!

This LoRA was trained to only do Aviator style sunglasses. I was going to include a bunch of different varieties (wraparound, circular, cat's eye, etc.) but this was way too much work. I now have a greater admiration for those brave souls who have given us LoRAs of buttholes pretty scenery.

DISCLAIMER: Sometimes you wont get any sunglasses, sometimes they wont be mirrored, sometimes they won't be aviators, sometimes they will be a mangled mess embedded in someone's skull. That's what INPAINTING is for. If you can't get a decent pair of shades with this LoRA, that's on you my friend.

Like my work? Buy me a beer!

and who knows, maybe I'll do something like this again someday.
